One Market Certainty "There is nothing like price to change sentiment." -- Divine Ms M There is perhaps but one market certainty. The consensus will almost always be Bullish (on global growth and financial asset prices) -- it is the nature of the Beast as bearishness is not in

their DNA. Moreover, most have a vested interest in higher stock prices. Remember this when you observe the herd's mantra of optimism. Buyers live higher and sellers live lower. By contrast I run my money and that of my investors based on a contrarian streak and a calculator.
My most important calculation is that of intrinsic value, which provides me with an opportunity to buy fear and sell greed, unemotionally.
